This document defines the operating constitution for the Product-driven (Shape Up) workspace.

## Purpose

```yaml
section: constitution.purpose
title: Purpose
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
tags: [purpose, governance]
```

To structure product development around shaped pitches, fixed-time cycles, and appetites, ensuring we only build well-defined ideas.

## Non-Negotiable Rules

```yaml
section: constitution.non-negotiable-rules
title: Non-Negotiable Rules
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
tags: [rules, governance]
```

* We do not build unshaped work. Every cycle project must refer to a pitch.
* Cycle deadlines are fixed-time; scope is variable. If a project isn't finished within the cycle, it is dropped by default (circuit breaker).
* Product decision logs and cycle specifications must be updated in `product/` memory.
* Changes to this constitution can only be approved by the owner.

## Cycle Management

```yaml
section: constitution.cycle-management
title: Cycle Management
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
cycle_duration_weeks: 6
cool_down_weeks: 2
tags: [cycle, shape-up]
```

* **Shaping**: Designing the work at the right level of abstraction (neither too high nor too detailed).
* **Betting**: Choosing which pitches to fund for the upcoming cycle.
* **Building**: Fixed 6-week cycles of uninterrupted development, followed by a 2-week cool-down.

## Definition of Done

```yaml
section: constitution.definition-of-done
title: Definition of Done
status: active
owner: "{{ owner }}"
required_checks:
  - pitch_approved_at_betting_table
  - scope_mapped
  - functional_demo_approved
  - decision_history_updated
  - test_suite_passing
tags: [dod, quality, validation]
```

To mark a product cycle project as `done`, the following must be met:

1. Pitch accepted at the betting table.
2. Core scopes mapped and completed.
3. Functional demo approved by the Product Owner.
4. Key decisions documented in `product/decisions.md`.
5. Existing test suite passes with zero failures.

